[30;1m94 | [0m[35m    # Should the validator switch `use_auth_token` values to `token`? In practice, always[0m
[30;1m95 | [0m[35m    # True in `huggingface_hub`. Might not be the case in a downstream library.[0m
[30;1m96 | [0m[35m    check_use_auth_token = "use_auth_token" not in signature.parameters and "token" in signature.par[0m
[30;1m97 | [0m[35m[0m

[30;1m29 | [0m[35mclass CommitScheduler:[0m
[30;1m30 | [0m[35m    """[0m
[30;1m31 | [0m[35m    Scheduler to upload a local folder to the Hub at regular intervals (e.g. push to hub every 5 min[0m
[30;1m32 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m33 | [0m[35m    The recommended way to use the scheduler is to use it as a context manager. This ensures that th[0m
[30;1m34 | [0m[35m    properly stopped and the last commit is triggered when the script ends. The scheduler can also b[0m
